<html>
	<head>
		<meta name="robots" content="noindex">
		<title>brand guidelines</title>
		<style>
			.divider{
				height: 6px;
				background-color: #D8E0E0;
				border-radius: 3px;
				margin: 45px 13px;
				box-shadow: 0 1.2px 5px 0px #00000026;
			}

			img{
				margin-top: 15px;
			}

			img,iframe{
				border-radius: 8px;
				max-width: 100%;
				box-shadow: 0px 0px 20px 0px #00000040;
				background-color: #0000001f;
			}

			/* styling */
			body {
				background: #4b7071;
				overflow-x: hidden;
			}
			* {
				font-family: 'Quicksand', 'Trebuchet MS', 'Helvetica Neue', HelveticaNeue, Arial, sans-serif;
				color: #d8e0e0;
			}
			a {
				color: #d8e0e0;
				text-decoration: underline;
				font-weight: bold;
			}
			body::-webkit-scrollbar {
				width: 12px;
			}
			body::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
				background-color: #4b7071;
			}
			body::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
				background-color: #d8e0e0;
				outline: none;
				border: 3px #4b7071 solid;
				border-radius: 6px;
			}

			/* center footer */
			.footer {
				text-align: center;
				margin: -5px auto 60px auto;
			}

			/* date */
			.art-date {
				margin: 30px 0 -28px 0;
				font-weight: bold;
			}

			/* headers */
			header h2 a {
				text-decoration: none;
				font-weight: normal;
			}
			header h2 a:hover {
				text-decoration: underline;
			}

			/* container width */
			.container {
				max-width: 800px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding-left: 1.5rem;
				paddint-right: 1.5rem;
				width: 100%;
			}

			/* center iframe */
			iframe {
				margin: auto;
				display: block;
				margin-bottom: -20px;
			}

			h1 {
				text-align: center;
				margin: 30px 0 15px 0;
			}

			h2 {
				margin: 20px 0;
			}

			h3 {
				margin: 40px 0 8px 0;
			}

			#colors {
				display: flex;
				justify-content: space-around;
				margin: 42px auto -6px auto;
				max-width: 600px;
			}

			.colortext {
				text-align: center;
				margin-top: 5px;
				font-weight: bold;
			}

			.colorcode {
				text-align: center;
				margin-bottom: 5px;
				opacity: .5;
			}

			.colorthing {
				width: 100px;
				height: 100px;
				border: 3px solid;
				border-radius: 100px;
				box-shadow: 0 1.2px 5px 0px #00000026;
			}

			.pikachu img {
				margin-right: 20px;
				margin-top: 5px;
				width: 100px;
				height: 100px;
			}

			.pikachu {
				display: inline-block;
			}

			.eevee {
				background-color: black;
			}

			.pokemon {
				display: inline-block;
				vertical-align: top;
				width: calc(100% - 130px);
			}

			code {
				font-family: "FreeMono", "Courier New", monospace;
				display: block;
				margin: 20px 10px;
				border-radius: 6px;
				border: 2px solid;
				padding: 2px 5px;
			}

			p, .p {
				margin: 0 0 16px 7px;
			}
		</style>
		<link rel="StyleSheet" id="quicksand" type="text/css" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Quicksand:500,700&display=swap">
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="container">
			<h1>unplugred brand guidelines</h1>
			<center style="opacity:.5">(please avoid linking this page)</center>
			<div class="divider"></div>
			<h2>tone</h2>
			<p>
conversational for the most part.<br/>
human and natural.<br/>
frequently engaged with other people, never political.
			</p>
			<p>
lowercase only for most things, names can be uppercase to improve readability.<br/>
no apostrophes on theyll theyre etc.<br/>
put apostrophes on she'll and he'll to avoid confusion.
			</p>
			<div class="divider"></div>
			<h2>logo</h2>
			<p>
there are four main versions of the logo.<br/>
they are ordered from best case scenario to worst case scenario.<br/>
start with the topmost version and go down until all conditions apply
			</p>
			<h3>antialiased transparent gif</h3>
			<div class="pikachu"><img class="eevee" src="/brand-guidelines/antialiased transparent gif thumbnail.gif"/></div>
			<div class="pokemon">
use this if:
				<ul>
<li>the background element's color is #4B7071</li>
<li>the site/program supports animated gifs</li>
<li>the site/program supports transparency</li>
<li>there will be no visible border around the image</li>
				</ul>
this can be created by downloading the opaque gif below, and then running the following command on <a href="https://imagemagick.org" target="_blank">ImageMagick</a>:
<code>magick convert -dispose background 'opaque gif.gif' -scale 100x100 -fuzz 1% -fill '#4B707100' -opaque '#4B7071FF' 'antialiased transparent gif.gif'</code>
be sure to replace 100x100 with the desired resolution<br/>
the antialiased transparent gif must be resized before using, as its entire point is to save bandwidth.<br/>
this gif is preferred over the opaque gif when the background is colored, because the gif color palette does not allow for an accurate enough color representation of the background color, and a slight edge might be seen.
			</div>
			<h3>aliased transparent gif</h3>
			<a class="pikachu" href="/brand-guidelines/aliased transparent gif.gif"><img class="eevee" src="/brand-guidelines/aliased transparent gif thumbnail.gif"/></a>
			<div class="pokemon">
use this if:
				<ul>
<li>the requirements for using the version above does not apply</li>
<li>the site/program supports animated gifs</li>
<li>the site/program supports transparency</li>
<li>there will be no visible border around the image</li>
				</ul>
be sure to resize the gif to the appropriate size before using it to save bandwidth.<br/>
gifs can be easily resized by running the following command on <a href="https://imagemagick.org" target="_blank">ImageMagick</a>:
<code>magick convert 'aliased transparent gif.gif' -scale 100x100 'aliased transparent gif resized.gif'</code>
be sure to replace 100x100 with the desired resolution
			</div>
			<h3>opaque gif</h3>
			<a class="pikachu" href="/brand-guidelines/opaque gif.gif"><img src="/brand-guidelines/opaque gif thumbnail.gif"/></a>
			<div class="pokemon">
use this if:
				<ul>
<li>the requirements for using the versions above does not apply</li>
<li>the site/program supports animated gifs</li>
				</ul>
be sure to resize the gif to the appropriate size before using it to save bandwidth.<br/>
gifs can be easily resized by running the following command on <a href="https://imagemagick.org" target="_blank">ImageMagick</a>:
<code>magick convert 'opaque gif.gif' -scale 100x100 'opaque gif resized.gif'</code>
be sure to replace 100x100 with the desired resolution
			</div>
			<h3>transparent png</h3>
			<a class="pikachu" href="/brand-guidelines/transparent png.png"><img class="eevee" src="/brand-guidelines/transparent png thumbnail.png"/></a>
			<div class="pokemon">
use this if:
				<ul>
<li>the requirements for using the versions above does not apply</li>
<li>the site/program supports transparency</li>
<li>there will be no visible border around the image</li>
				</ul>
be sure to resize the image to the appropriate size before using it to save bandwidth.
			</div>
			<h3>opaque png</h3>
			<a class="pikachu" href="/brand-guidelines/opaque png.png"><img src="/brand-guidelines/opaque png thumbnail.png"/></a>
			<div class="pokemon">
use this if:
				<ul>
<li>the requirements for using the versions above does not apply</li>
				</ul>
be sure to resize the image to the appropriate size before using it to save bandwidth.
			</div><br/><br/><br/>
			<p>
images must be resized with Fant sampling if you are using Paint.net, -scale if you are using ImageMagick, and Cubic if you are using GIMP.
			</p>
			<div class="divider"></div>
			<h2>color</h2>
			<p>
the palette consists of 3 main colors.<br/>
other colors should be used tastefully.
			</p>
			<div id="colors">
				<div class="color">
					<div style="background-color:#4B7071" class="colorthing"></div>
					<div class="colortext">Background</div>
					<div class="colorcode">#4B7071</div>
				</div>
				<div class="color">
					<div style="background-color:#D8E0E0" class="colorthing"></div>
					<div class="colortext">Foreground</div>
					<div class="colorcode">#D8E0E0</div>
				</div>
				<div class="color">
					<div style="background-color:#91A8A8" class="colorthing"></div>
					<div class="colortext">Subtitles</div>
					<div class="colorcode">#91A8A8</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="divider"></div>
			<h2>font</h2>
			<p>
the font used on pages and elements that use the brand logo and palette should use the Quicksand font.<br/>
<a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Quicksand">the font is available to download at Google Fonts and can be freely used for personal and commercial purposes.</a><br/>
use medium weight (500) for most text and <b>bold (700) for highlights/titles that demand it.</b><br/>
other weights can be explored with caution on more unusual layouts, though keep page loading speed in mind when working for web.
			</p>
			<p style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', 'Helvetica Neue', HelveticaNeue, Arial, sans-serif">
when unable to use custom downloaded fonts,<br/>
use the Trebuchet font that comes with most PC and Mac systems.
			</p>
			<p style="font-family: sans-serif">
as a last resort, use a basic sans serif such as Arial or Helvetica.
			</p>
			<div class="divider"></div>
			<h2>layout and design</h2>
			<h3>dividers</h3>
			<p>
use 6 pixel wide lines with rounded corners to divide between content (just like on this page).<br/>
dividers can be both horizontal and vertical.
			</p>
			<h3>media</h3>
			<div class="p">
images, videos, and other media that <b>ISNT</b> transparent should have
			<ul>
<li>an 8 pixels rounded corner</li>
<li>a shadow with 20 pixels spread and 25% opacity</li>
<li>a black background with 12% opacity to seamlessly match the shadows (to serve as a placeholder when the image still loads)</li>
			</ul>
			</div>
			<h3>shadows</h3>
			<p>
small items that arent media should have a small box shadow with a spread of 5 pixels, that is 1.2 pixels down on the Y axis, and an opacity of 15%.<br/>
this includes also the divider.
			</p>
			<h3>links</h3>
			<p>
links should be colored the same as the text, be bold, and have an underline.
			</p>
			<h3>love</h3>
			<p>
love is important, give love to your page.
			</p>
			<h3>layout</h3>
			<p>
layouts should be linear, and read either top to bottom or left to right.<br/>
on left to right layouts the logo should be around the left side of the screen and centered vertically.<br/>
on top to bottom layouts the logo should be around the top of the screen and centered horizontally.<br/>
make sure the layout is airy and breathing, with plenty of margin between objects, dividers, and lots of margin on the sides of the page to keep the layout confined.
			</p>
			<div class="divider"></div>
		</div>
	</body>
